cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper presents a novel approach for bundle-specific tractography using diffusion MRI tractograms. This involves the use of tract orientation mapping (TOM) and accurate segmentations of the tract outline and its start and end region. The paper also introduces a custom probabilistic tracking algorithm. These techniques are all related to computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM).
